The M7.0 #Peru #earthquake occurred as the result of normal faulting ~260 km beneath SE Peru within the lithosphere of the subducting Nazca plate. To learn more about the tectonics of this region watch https://t.co/t5krfffnOG https://t.co/AedFiQeYN6
In 2011, the M9 #Japan #earthquake ruptured a fault area 500kms x 200kms over an interval of nearly 3 min. Surveys of sea-floor bathymetry before and after the earthquake document up to 50 m of fault displacement at near the Japan Trench. https://t.co/ZsD4gnhgfq
Western South America is a region of high #earthquake hazard bc of:
• Tsunami-generating megathrust earthquakes on the Nazca –South America plate boundary 
• Major eqs w/in the subducting plate beneath populated coastal towns
• Major eqs on faults w/in the continental crust. https://t.co/j1utMAqiPG

🔴明日の地震予測7日夜

小地震時々地震M6

女満別　40🔴
柿岡       34⭕
鹿屋     30△

9日夕方から夜にM6予測。確率60％

群馬・長野・埼玉県境付近で、震度２相当のようです。 #jishin #earthquake #地震
根室沖で、こんなにはっきりと「プレート境界」その場所で、
大きめな地震（M6クラス）は久々だと思う。

もう少し大きければ震度５クラスの津波も警戒レベルだし、

Ranked as a "Shindo 4" quake in some parts of Hokkaido, this quake is probably not large enough to have done large-scale damage, though it was approaching that level. No tsunami is expected. (MP) #Hokkaido #Nemuro #Earthquake
The quake is now said to have been centered off the coast of Hokkaido and is downgraded to 6.2 magnitude. (MP) #Hokkaido #Nemuro #Earthquake

An #earthquake in #Maharashtra measuring 4.3 on the Richter scale struck #Palghar on Friday morning. No loss of life reported. The depth of the quake was 5 km. Since November 2018, the region has been hit by some 30 low-intensity earthquakes with Friday’s being the strongest.

GPS/GNSS time series from #Mayotte stations. Here from IGN.

The time series are detrended (i.e. without motion relative to IGS ref. frame). Shows progressive, still ongoing, E-ward and downward motion (&gt;10cm) since May 2018, thus toward offshore #earthquake swarm. https://t.co/ddaSSm8aB2
